what is DOM ?
    DOM stands for " Document Object MOdel : it is a structured
    Representation of HTML Documnets, it allows Javascript
    to manipulate them

DOM is connection between HTML DOcuments and javascript code
DOM is automatically created by the Browser as soon as HTML page is loaded
DOM is stored in a tree like structre, generated by browser

DOM tree always start with Document object 
    eg:- document.querySelector()
it is a special object that is the entry point to the DOM

DOM !== Javascript
DOM is a part of Web APIs